%N A394607 Decimal expansion of the mode of the distribution of distances between two points in a unit square.
%C A394607 The mode of the probability density function f(x) = 4*x*(Pi/2 - 2*x + x^2/2) for x <= 1, and 4*x*(arcsin(1/x) - arccos(1/x) + 2*sqrt(x^2-1) - (x^2+2)/2) for 1 <= x <= sqrt(2) (Ghosh, 1951).
%H A394607 Birendranath Ghosh, <a href="https://archive.org/details/dli.calcutta.11610/page/17/mode/1up">Random distances within a rectangle and between two rectangles</a>, Bulletin of Calcutta Mathematical Society, Vol. 43 (1951), pp. 17-24.
%H A394607 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/SquareLinePicking.html">Square Line Picking</a>.
%H A394607 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A394607 Equals (4 - sqrt(16-3*Pi))/3.
%e A394607 0.478593474322897321466327136807682681798469556800526...
%t A394607 RealDigits[(4 - Sqrt[16-3*Pi])/3, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A394607 (PARI) (4 - sqrt(16-3*Pi))/3
